runs.comm: fuller one just outside of off which is squirted away towards the cover fielder, with the eventual misfield affording Raza the luxury of getting off the mark
gets nicely behind this fullish length outside of off
guilty of straying on the pads as this is glanced away behind of square
defends this back of a length outside of off with soft hands
slipping down leg as there appears to be a sound as it went by, but called wide by the umpire
again heading down the leg side as Regis is able to get it away for a single
squirts away a length delivery through third man which nibbles away a touch on off stump
delivers a full, wide delivery which is sliced away through backward point, who puts in a vain dive up and to his right to try and stop this
length delivery which gets good carry as it took off the deck
able to dab away this back of a length outside of off through third man

length delivery on middle and off which appears to strike in line. The umpire is not interested, as it looked like there may be an inside-edge on it. Holder is interested though, and wants a review. There doesn't appear to be an obvious deflection, but the only thing now is height, with the replays confirming the ball would go on to hit the leg stump, so a great review in the end by the WI captain. Regis has to go with not too much on the board
short of a length and cramping him for room a touch as he just about gets a tickle to the leg side to steal a single
shortish length outside off which is lifted over the extra-cover fielder to find the boundary in the deep
gets an outside edge to this length delivery which streaks away to the third man region
length delivery, closer to the batsman, which is allowed to sail through to the keeper
short of a length and defended to the off side
follows the line of this fuller one pitched up outside of off, with this deviating away upon pitching
length ball coming into the batsman, Masakadza misses the flick and is hit on the pads. However, that was sliding down leg
length delivery on off, Masakadza gets forward and drives firmly, straight to the man at mid-off
looks to push this one through the off side, but ends up mistiming to the leg side
goes for the old dab-and-run outside of off, with Raza making a late decision for the call as he went through to the other end
shoulders arms to this back of a length which shapes away outside off
content to let this short of a length sail through to the keeper
tucked away off the pads as he bowls this a bit too straight
tries to force one away through the off side now, but is stopped by the fielder at point
ends up defending back to the bowler in his follow through
tries to get this away off the pads, but this ends up near mid-on
succeeds in getting Hamilton's edge, but this dies quickly on the first slip, who never really had a chance
helps ease the anxiety with a chip over extra-cover to pickup a vital boundary
angling in on the batsman as he just about gets bat on this to works this away on the off side for a quick single

Hamilton looking for the big heave through midwicket as he looks to be late on this one on middle and leg. Looked out initially, but Hamilton wants the review. Nothing on Snicko and replays confirm that this was indeed plumb in front. Not a good review at all as they waste this one. Original decision stands
defended away off the back foot towards the off side
gets deep in the crease to keep out this length delivery on middle and off
gets nicely behind the line of this length delivery on off stump
class from Raza. Able to punch away a drive through the extra-cover region which just races away to the boundary
now picks his spot at square-leg to get away this short delivery with an authoritative pull
this time slaps away through the gap between cover and point, but just can't quite get it past the inner ring
back of a length and coming back into the batsman, Taylor defends it, with the ball dropping onto the off side. He wants a quick single, but decides against it
short of a length and allowed to sail through outside off to the keeper
beautiful delivery from Jerome Taylor! That was pretty close to the off stump as Brendan Taylor let it through
defended from the confines of his crease towards the off side
angling down leg as Taylor fails to get any bat on this to tickle it down leg
plays at this length delivery with an angled face as this is dabbed down to third man
shortish length which rises on him as he just about fends this away
nudges away this length delivery on the pads as they are able to pickup a brace behind square
gets under this shorter one from Holder which climbs quite appreciably. Called one for the over
angling down leg as this one is tucked away behind square
able to tuck away Holder softly on the leg side for a quick single

banged in short by Holder! It takes Taylor by surprised, he jumps into the crease and looks to fend, the ball brushes the forearm and goes over the keeper to the fine leg fence. That was very vicious!
fires a bouncer which is called wide by the umpire after the earlier transgressions from the bowler

looking for quick runs with a ramp over third man, but ends up hitting it squarer to the fielder positioned in the deep in that area. Lendl Simmons is able to get himself settled under it to take it safely. Zimbabwe now three down, and Raza, who looked the most threatening, has to go
great take from Ramdin to his left as this one catches the thigh pad on the way to the keeper down leg
driven on the up through the off side, but picks out the man at point
Taylor looks to get away a boundary through third man with a glide, but is stopped before the rope by the man in the deep stationed there
gets away with this streaky slice through point, with the fielder tracking it back before the boundary rope
fullish length which is driven down to mid-off as Williams gets his tally going
looking to get this one past point, but doesn't quite time it away off the middle
defended back to the bowler as this drifts in from outside off
punches it to long on for a comfortable single
glanced away on the leg side, but picks out square-leg
Taylor goes for the reverse sweep, misses, and the ball goes off the pad towards fine leg
gets away a single through mid-on to get to the other end
drives this one straight back to the bowler to end a tight opening over from Miller
slides in on middle as this is nudged away to the leg side
flights one in to Sean who is able to lean into a drive, with this one ending up at long off
drags this one just outside of off as this is deflected away by the batsman
looking to steal a single on the leg side with a dab, but is held by the close-in fielder
flighted in and respected by Brendan on the front foot
takes a few steps down before lofting Marlon over his head to end up in the hands of long on after a couple of bounces
forces away the spinner through long on to get Brendan on strike
defended carefully from his crease
able to direct this one away through the covers for one
steers the spinner to long on once more
realises there is no one in the deep at backward square/long leg, so targets the area with a paddle over the region which carries far enough to sail over the rope
guides this next delivery sensibly to extra-cover to end the over
turned away on the leg side for a single
backs away a touch, but can't force away a shot on the off side
swipes one away on the leg side to get Brendan on strike
gets forward to defend this one drifted in from Samuels
glanced away off the pads behind square for a quick single
sweeps this one round the corner to deep backward square
picks his spot at deep extra-cover, and then lofts the spinner classically over the region to pickup a boundary, despite the despairing dive from Sammy
this time frees his arms to cut away through extra-cover
steered down past the bowler to long on
afforded width, but can't punish it despite cutting this away through point
content to ease this one down to long off
driven away through the leg side to end the over
lovely shimmy down the pitch before lofting the bowler aerially through cover to pickup a boundary
now gets away a single through midwicket
turned away to the leg side by Brendan for a straightforward single
looks to pickup a quick single on the off side, but hits it a bit too well to the fielder
places this one beautifully behind of square with a sweep to find the boundary
steers one away through cover now to keep the strike
looking to be cheeky with the reverse sweep, but doesn't quite come off to plan
gets a top-edge to this sweep, with this landing safely in the end at deep fine leg
fantastic reverse sweep to this one drifted in from outside off as this is rocketed away to the third man boundary. Brings up the fifty-run stand as well
looks to force one off the back foot, but ends up finding short mid-on
completely misses the ball as he attempts to sweep this round the corner
punched back straight to the bowler to end the over
steers away a single through long on
fended back to the bowler in his follow through

down the track to this one floated in outside off as he chips this over extra-cover, but is not able to do enough for this to reach the rope. Replays show that the fielder may have just grazed the rope with his foot when he was there in the deep to field it, so ruled four runs in the end
drags the length outside off as this is crunched away to sweeper cover
tries to glance this one past the leg slip, but ends up hitting it to the man
just about gets away the spinner through backward square
gets away a bottom-edge through fine leg as this one was short and wide for him to go after, but didn't get it away

Williams has continued his good from the other match as he times this one to perfection as he shimmied a bit before meeting this with a firm push to just thread this past mid-off, who was looking to slide in to try and stop the ball
now gets away a whip through midwicket for one
advances down the track, with the ball crashing into the pad of the batsman, but he was far too down the pitch to get a decent shout in
this time Brendan unfurls the reverse sweep, managing to bissect the gap between point and gully to find the boundary
defended back to the bowler to end the over
tries to clatter Samuels through the covers before readjusting to stroke this down to long off
looking to be cute with another reverse sweep, but is struck just outside
looking to create room to force this away on the leg side, but ends up hitting ti back to the bowler
steered away on the off side towards backward point
able to force away a boundary past short backward square to pickup a valuable boundary
once again looking to get away the sweep, with this one still getting away through the same region, but not as quickly this time
begins with a length delivery across the batsman which is driven towards extra-cover
back of a length and defended by the batsman off the back foot
short ball which Brendan just about gets out of the way from, but only just as he falls over after in an attempt to balance himself
dabs away a single through backward point
tries to steer this one past point, but to no avail
short enough for him to pull, but ends up finding the boundary rider at deep midwicket

Brendan, looking to paddle this through fine leg, ends up top-edging a chance to Ramdin, with the WI celebrating. The umpire, though, doesn't appear moved, but Ramdin and Marlon want this reviewed. Brendan didn't seem too perturbed though, and why not since replays show that this indeed went off the forearm, and not glove. But hang on, this has been given out, and I am a bit shocked as there didn't seem to be clear evidence there for this to be given out conclusively.. but the decision has come down. Brendan has to go after his fine 37

leans out to this pitched outside off, hitting this away to the off side in order to set off for a quick single. Williams just about makes his ground despite having to go in for the dive after the close-in fielder took a shy at his stumps
able to get away a slap through the covers for a couple
defended on the front foot by the batsman
punched away now towards mid-off, who does well to stop it with a dive to his right
eases into a drive through long off to end a successful over for West Indies
full, and wide of off as this is sliced away through backward point. Also gets him to his fifty, following his 70-odd from the previous match against the UAE
excellent fielding at backward point to stop this blitz from Ervine
gets away an aerial stroke through third man, with the fielder waiting for it just before the rope
short outside off which the batsman is late on as he tried to clatter through the line, but Russell has overstepped, with a free hit called for the next ball
ends up hitting this one straight up in the air, but the bowler has gone over the mark once more. Holder not too amused
fires in a short one now outside of off as Russell is losing a bit of focus here. Free hit once more
pitches it up now, and he is punished by Williams as he lifts the fast bowler down the ground to the vacant area at long on
this time steered down to mid-on by Williams
forces one away off the back foot through point to end this nine-ball over finally
gets down the track but mistimes the slog away to long on
tries to guide this one away through point, but to no avail
another one he looks to force through, but picks out the same fielder
leans forward now as this is fended away softly to the off side
defended off the back foot and from the relative safety of his crease
short-arm jab past the bowler to keep the strike
glides this short of a length away through third man
tries to blaze away through the covers, but doesn't quite come off for him
too full and on the pads as Williams flicks this away effortlessly through midwicket to pickup four. Williams is the man WI want removed
now targets square-leg with a powerful pull, but Simmons, who is at the boundary, is able to stop this with a neat, sliding dive
authoritative pull through midwicket which is stopped by Lendl before the rope
short ball which tapers away as the batsman lets it through to the keeper
slapped away hard through to deep extra-cover as Ervine is brought on strike
carted away hard through midwicket, but finds silly mid-on
this time cut away on the off side, but can't force it through
uses his feet well to come down and slam Samuels over mid-on to pickup four valuable runs
places this next one through cow corner now with a pull, wanting two runs from the get-go
this time carved away square off the wicket to bring the over to a close
starts round the wicket as this is defended away on the front foot
turned away to the leg side now for a quick single
short outside off and allowed to go through to the keeper as he weaved out of its path
defended away off the back foot now by the batsman
able to glide this one away off the top of the bounce through the third man region
nudges this one away square off the wicket to end the over
flatter and wider from Samuels. Williams cuts it straight to the fielder at extra-cover
defends this one sliding in from outside off towards the off side
eases away a single through the off side to rotate the strike
sweeps this one going down leg round the corner, just beating the boundary rider coming in from deep square-leg
picks his gap at cow corner before powering away a pull through the region, with this one just having enough legs on it to reach the boundary rope
cut away now, in front of point, to the man out at deep cover
continues from round the wicket as Ervine is late on this off cutter
slants this one on leg as Ervine is able to help this behind square
fuller one off the pads which is clipped away to square-leg. Also brings up the fifty-run stand between these two. The second in as many matches to add to their 83-run stand against the UAE
able to nurdle a single down the leg side to get Williams on strike

banged in from Holder from round the wicket as Williams' stay at the crease comes to an end after he mistimes a pull through midwicket, with the blade turning in his hands. Ends up going up straight to midwicket who is able to take it comfortably. Ends another crucial hand from Williams, and one suspects that with that wicket, the chase may have slipped away out of Zimbabwe's hands..
fuller one which is dug out towards mid-on to end a successful over for the West Indians
back of a length, just outside off, which is defended by the batsman
fuller one now which just slips under the bat of Stuart as he tried to dig it out
gets this one horribly wrong as he splays down the leg side
swinging delivery on middle and off which is countered effectively by Stuart
another one slipping down the leg side as the umpire gets to stretch his arms
rocks forward slightly to defend this length delivery just outside off

fires a quick bouncer outside of off which catches Stuart's blade as he went for the ramp. Doesn't go all the way to the boundary with third man coming round to field it. Seemed to surprise Stuart as this went through
tries out the yorker now which Stuart is more than equal to
continues from round the wicket as Ervine leans into a drive down the ground to find a boundary through long on

lovely flick from Ervine, this one going over square-leg, as Holder seemed to want to follow the batsman, but gave the leg-side angle he needed to get this away. Flies all the way over for a 71-metre six
dabs this one through the third man region to pickup a single

almost drags on this Holder length delivery from outside of off, but Stuart is able to get away it as he hares down to the other end after seeing Ervine making a bee-line for the striker's end. Holder gets there in what seems like three, gigantic paces, but can't kick the ball onto the stumps
short enough for Ervine to get after as he pulls this one competently through backward square for a boundary
looks for the dab-and-run through third man, but is sent back by his partner when he sees backward point coming after it. The fielder is able to fire in a throw, but the batsman makes his ground
skids the ball onto Stuart, who is able to tuck this away through long on for a quick single
looking to reverse sweep this one drifting in from outside off, but is late on it
gets away a stroke through the covers to pickup a couple. Gets them to 200 as well

dropped Ervine, with lovely use of the feet, is able to loft the bowler straight down through long on, with Taylor, running in to his left, unable to hold on to the chance as this bursts through, before continuing on to the boundary
defended by the batsman
nurdles a single down to long on

starts from round the wicket and is greeted with a disdainful flick over square-leg which doesn't quite carry all the way as he would have liked. Ends up being fielded by the fielder stationed there in the deep
length, wide of off, which is crashed away through the covers, beating the man from deep cover to the boundary
slower ball drifted through which is eased away to mid-off
dipping full toss which is struck back to Sammy on the full, who is able to stop this with a hand in his follow through
slower delivery going down middle and leg which is hit uppishly towards the short backward square, but falls short in the end
is late on this one pitched wide of off as he tries to get a bat to it
is on the money straightaway with this length delivery just outside off which is defended by the batsman
fuller one slipping down leg which is penalised by the umpire
overpitched on middle and leg and punished as this is struck back down the ground for four
glides away this back of a length outside of off through third man for one
bissects the gap between fine leg and square leg with a powerful hook through the region to bring up his fifty in just 37 balls. Has kept his team just in this I reckon, but he still has plenty to do
delivers a bumper which Ervine does not seem interested to tangle with
short and trying to cramp him for room as this is hooked quickly to fine leg
darts in one on the pads which is glanced away towards midwicket
slipping down leg as this is paddled hard to short backward square, who is able to get his body behind it
looking to turn this one away off the pads, but ends up running the leg bye as he fails to make contact

you knew it was going to happen as Gayle strikes in his very first over itself. Ervine, looking to fetch this from outside of off, ends up playing all around as the ball turns in sharply to castle his off stump. The danger-man Ervine goes for 52, and Zimbabwe stare down the prospect of an inevitable defeat
content to just fend away this one darted in on middle and leg
gets a single away to the leg side, before an errant throw from the deep allows them the opportunity to return for a second
short outside of off which is ramped away rather awkwardly towards third man
angles in this fuller one which is inside-edged away through fine leg
gets away a club through midwicket, but only just as it may have hit high on the splice of the bat as he went through with the shot
fires in a bouncer which beats Stuart for pace as he tried to clobber this one out of the Manuka Oval
helps this along with the angle with a whip of the pads behind square
drives away the pacer through to mid-off before setting off for a quick single
gives this one plenty of air as this just slips down leg, but is not penalised by the umpire
slow through the air as Stuart just about manages to get this away towards short backward square
continues with the same line as this is worked away to the same fielder
Gayle celebrates once more as he rushes this one on middle and off, with the batsman playing all around. With no reviews left, Stuart has to go
sliding down leg as this strikes low on the front pad. The batsmen end up running the leg bye anyways
drifts one in from outside off as this is struck back to the bowler
gets away a single through cover after the initial misfield by Jonathan Carter
searching for the blockhole as Elton just about digs this one out towards mid-on
trying for the yorker but ends up dishing a low full toss which is struck away towards the off side
another yorker which is safely negotiated by the batsman as this is squirted away to the off side
dishes up a full toss as he searches for the full delivery, with this one worked away to long off
fails to get away this bludgeon through the leg side, with this one finishing up at mid-on
looks to advance down the track before adjusting his stroke to nurdle this one away to the leg side
given plenty of air as this is cross-batted away through to deep midwicket
guided away to the man at long on for one

sliding down leg as this strikes the pads. Gayle goes for the appeal, but the umpire remained nonplussed. And at the eleventh hour, the WI have gone for the review. This one strikes pretty full on the boot, with no indication of any inside-edge. Wickets do show to be umpire's call, but because it was given not out initially, the original decision stands
Elton celebrates the reprieve by shimmying down before launching Gayle high over cow corner for six
tries to blast one away through the off side, but ends up hitting it back to the bowler in his follow through

Tinashe unable to drop his wrists in time to this one which rears up on a short of a length outside of off . The ball ends up catching the gloves on the way through to Ramdin, who takes it comfortably at chest height
tests him with a shorter one that has the batsman ducking for cover
called one more for the over as he delivers yet another sharp bouncer which the batsman is not willing to engage with
searching for the base of middle and leg as this is driven away towards long on
full delivery, wide of off, which looks like the batsman may have edged to as he went after it, but the umpire says no contact
searching for the wide yorker, but ends up straddling too far over the line
pushes at this length delivery towards the off side to end the over

looks to run this one past the backward point, taking on the fielder as soon as he dabbed it towards him. The non-striker is able to make his ground in the nick of time before the flat throw. They do a review just to confirm, but Elton definitely made it through
backs away before squeezing away this fuller one on middle and leg towards backward point
tries to sweep one away round the corner, but is late on it

chips the spinner just over midwicket, before just getting to the boundary rope in the deep, despite Jonathan Carter putting in a splendid dive to try and save runs for his team. He grazed the rope as he attempted to flick the ball away
gives this plenty of air on middle as this is dug out successfully by the batsman
good change of pace to draw the batsman slightly forward to this one pushed through outside off
full delivery which is lofted over to long off, albeit mistimed, as this lands a couple of feet before the fielder
goes down a track a few steps before striking this one straight to the mid-off fielder
slow yorker just outside off which is squirted away towards deep cover
gets away the bowler through the leg side for a quick single

you just can't keep him out of the action tonight as he now adds his name to the catches column, picking off this aerial chip from Elton at extra-cover, before finishing with a couple of dramatic rolls to get the crowd off their feet. Zimbabwe now nine down as West Indies look to complete the last rites
survives this fuller one on middle and off to push this away to the off side
fires a wide down the leg side which the batsmen also take a run on as it beats the keeper as well
slows this one down outside of off as this catches the face to bobble ever so slightly on the off side
flighted beautifully outside off as this is eased away down to long off
tries to force one past the bowler, but Chris hurries onto it
parries away the bowler down to long on
fires in a quicker one which is signalled wide by the umpire
goes round the wicket now to Kamungozi, who defends off the back foot
backs away to try and clear Gayle over extra-cover, but misses out when he goes through for the stroke
Chatara gets away with this mistimed pull, with this flying over the keeper's head, who tried to get to it, but falls in the deep at fine leg
ramps this short, wide delivery to the man stationed out at third man
ducks under this shorter one on middle and leg
drives this fuller one to the man at mid-off before haring down to the non-striker's
follows the batsman as he sees him coming down the track, with this one angling leg-side as Chatara reared his head out of the way
digs out this yorker speared in on leg-stump, getting this one away through to deep fine leg
given enough width to cut outside his off stump, which he does with ease as Chatara finds the boundary
goes round the wicket now as Chatara can do no better than strike this one back to Gayle
this time gets it away more towards midwicket, but picks out the fielder
once again looking to force it through the region, this time to find long on
gives this plenty of rip as Kamungozi ends up hitting this behind of square on the leg side
ends the over with a fortuitous boundary through cow corner which he gets away rather abruptly
fires one down the leg side, before straightening, but is called a wide
another one he gets wrong as he is penalised once more
defended with the bat, and softly to the leg side
chips away the bowler through to deep midwicket, running a brace in the process
and Miller sneaks through the gate to wrap up a convincing 73-run victory over Zimbabwe. This one drifted in, with the batsman leaving daylight between bat and pad
